The Proposal:
Centrally Sponsored Deendayal Antyodaya Yojana - National Urban Livelihoods Mission (DAY-NRLM)
NULM) was abolished and replaced by the "Deendayal Jan Aajeevika Yojana-Urban" scheme in the country.
The central government has decided to implement (as a guideline). This is on a pilot basis.
The implementation has been communicated under the letter dated 16.06.2025 to the Central Government. According to this plan,
It is being implemented on a pilot basis in the Kalyan-Dombivali Municipal Corporation in the state.
Allocation of funds for Central and State share of Deendayal Jan Aajeevika Yojana-Urban
The government was considering creating a new accounting title to do so.
The government's decision:
Centrally Sponsored "Deendayal Jan Aajeevika Yojana (Urban) (D-JAY (s)) in the State
To allocate funds for the Central share and State share of the scheme for implementation.
Approval is being given to open a new account title as follows.
